edu.umn.biomedicus.acronym

Interface SenseVectors

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    HashSenseVectors, RocksDBSenseVectors

    public SenseVectors

    Interface for the mapping of strings expansions to the sparse vector of their contexts.

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Default Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      boolean containsSense()
      Checks if the sense has an associated sparse vector.
      SparseVector get()
      Retrieves the context vector for the given sense.
      void removeWord()
      Removes the given word from this sense vectors object. May not be supported in certain implementations
      void removeWords()
      Removes a collection of words from this sense vectors object. May not be supported in certain implementations.
      java.util.Set<java.lang.String> senses()
      Returns a set of all the senses in this map.
      int size()
      Returns the total number of sense -> context mappings in this object.

      Returns a collection of all the context vectors in this map.

      • containsSense

        boolean containsSense()

        Checks if the sense has an associated sparse vector.

        Returns:

        Retrieves the context vector for the given sense.
